rComments: If you take a language course with this guy, you will suffer. He is disrespectful and does not care who you are. He talks behind your back with his colleagues, when he has the chance to. If he does not like you, he will make sure you will hate his course. If you can, drop his class immediately and spare yourself misery.

No office hours, but straightforward course. Well prepared lecturer; you could depend on him to deliver material in an interesting enough way if you enjoy Classics. Final was difficult but his instructions on the format were clear and useful.

While his lectures were entertaining and he did offer extra help, he was an excruciatingly hard marker. It was a little deceptive because his tests were not too difficult, however he took marks off for every little error, and even when there was only a more optimal translation. As a whole, on paper your efforts will go unrewarded.
Really a great prof. He knows his stuff, answers questions well, fair evaluations, and good sense of humour. I plan to take more classes with him.

This prof is absolutely what you want in any professor. He knows what he is talking about, enjoys it, ALWAYS makes it interesting and often comical. You really feel as though he is your friend, which is impressive in such a large class. He is very clear and tests are straightforward. No curve balls. Fantastic guy- GO TO HIS LECTURES!
